<P>
<H2>
<P>Transactions</H2>We make transaction information available in two formats: 
<OL>
  <LI>As a database that can be downloaded as compressed ".zip" file archive. 
  This form requires additional processing and intended for use by researchers 
  rather than fans wanting find information on-line. 
  <LI>A list for each year that shows nicely on your screen. It can be printed, 
  and there are links to our pages about the players and teams involved. 
</LI></OL>
<HR>

<H3>Database</H3>The <A 
href="https://www.retrosheet.org/transactions/readme.txt">read me file</A> 
describes the layout of the records and discusses what is and is not in the 
files and related topics. For your convenience, this file is included in the 
transaction data download. 
<P>There are three data files, each organized somewhat differently. They are 
designed for further processing and/or searching using tools such as a database 
program, spreadsheet program, or your own custom written program. The data files 
and the read me file are combined into one "zip" archive file, whose size is 
about 1 Mb. 
<P><A href="https://www.retrosheet.org/transactions/tranDB.zip">Download 
transaction file archive</A> 
<HR>

